Define the sample in bcgsfhs_sample.sex.  Use read_bcgsfhs_sample() to
read it.

* Sky-subtract and pre-process the mosaics:
  bcgsfhs_skysubtract

* Cut out and write just the BCG image and model:
  bcgsfhs_get_bcg, /debug

* Ellipse-fit the BCGs; make QAplots
  bcgsfhs_ellipse
  qaplots_bcgsfhs_ellipse

* Fit Sersic models to the surface-brightness profiles and compute
  radial aperture photometry from which we will model the SEDs in
  radial bins 
   bcgsfhs_sersicfit, /dofit, /dophot, /qaplot
   qaplot_bcgsfhs_seds - plot the SEDs


### Paper plots ###

* plotbcgsfhs_montage - build a nice color montage

* plotbcgsfhs_sbprofiles - surface brightness profiles + Sersic
  function fits overlaid

* plotbcgsfhs_ssps - build some simple SSPs; overlay the (K-corrected)
  BCG photometry and the models on a color-color plot

  


